{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Dogs have interests."},{"time":2000,"text":"They have interest sniffing each other, chasing squirrels."},{"time":8000,"text":"And if we don't make that a reward in training, that will be a distraction."},{"time":13000,"text":"It's always sort of struck me as really a scary thought"},{"time":18000,"text":"that if you see a dog in a park, and the owner is calling it,"},{"time":22000,"text":"and the owner says, you know, \"Puppy, come here, come here,\""},{"time":25000,"text":"and the dog thinks, \"Hmm, interesting."},{"time":28000,"text":"I'm sniffing this other dog's rear end, the owner's calling.\""},{"time":32000,"text":"It's a difficult choice, right?"},{"time":34000,"text":"Rear end, owner. Rear end wins."},{"time":36000,"text":"I mean, you lose."},{"time":38000,"text":"You cannot compete with the environment,"},{"time":41000,"text":"if you have an adolescent dog's brain."},{"time":43000,"text":"So, when we train, we're always trying to take into account"},{"time":47000,"text":"the dog's point of view."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49000,"text":"Now, I'm here largely because"},{"time":51000,"text":"there's kind of a rift in dog training at the moment"},{"time":54000,"text":"that -- on one side, we have people who think that you train a dog,"},{"time":58000,"text":"number one, by making up rules, human rules."},{"time":62000,"text":"We don't take the dog's point of view into account."},{"time":64000,"text":"So the human says, \"You're going to act this way, damn it."},{"time":67000,"text":"We're going to force you to act against your will, to bend to our will.\""},{"time":71000,"text":"Then, number two, we keep these rules a secret from the dog."},{"time":74000,"text":"And then number three, now we can punish the dog"},{"time":77000,"text":"for breaking rules he didn't even know existed."},{"time":80000,"text":"So you get a little puppy, he comes. His only crime is he grew."},{"time":84000,"text":"When he was a little puppy, he puts his paws on your leg --"},{"time":87000,"text":"you know, isn't that nice?"},{"time":89000,"text":"And you go, \"Oh, there's a good boy.\""},{"time":91000,"text":"You bend down, you pat him -- you reward him for jumping up."},{"time":95000,"text":"His one mistake is he's a Tibetan mastiff, and a few months later,"},{"time":99000,"text":"he weighs, you know, 80 pounds."},{"time":102000,"text":"Every time he jumps up, he gets all sorts of abuse."},{"time":105000,"text":"I mean, it is really very, very scary the abuse that dogs get."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110000,"text":"So, this whole dominance issue -- number one,"},{"time":114000,"text":"what we get in dog training is this Mickey-Mouse interpretation"},{"time":117000,"text":"of a very complicated social system."},{"time":120000,"text":"And they take this stuff seriously."},{"time":122000,"text":"Male dogs are very serious about a hierarchy,"},{"time":124000,"text":"because it prevents physical fights."},{"time":127000,"text":"Of course, female dogs, bitches, on the other hand,"},{"time":130000,"text":"have several bitch amendments to male hierarchical rule."},{"time":133000,"text":"The number one is, \"I have it, you don't.\""},{"time":135000,"text":"And what you will find is a very, very low-ranking bitch"},{"time":139000,"text":"will quite easily keep a bone away from a high-ranking male."},{"time":143000,"text":"So, we get in dog training this notion of dominances,"},{"time":146000,"text":"or of the alpha dog. I'm sure that you've heard this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149000,"text":"Dogs get so abused."},{"time":151000,"text":"Dogs, horses and humans --"},{"time":153000,"text":"these are the three species which are so abused in life."},{"time":156000,"text":"And the reason is built into their behavior --"},{"time":158000,"text":"is to always come back and apologize."},{"time":161000,"text":"Like, \"Oh, I'm sorry you had to beat me. I'm really sorry, yes, it's my fault.\""},{"time":164000,"text":"They are just so beatable,"},{"time":166000,"text":"and that's why they get beaten."},{"time":168000,"text":"The poor puppy jumps up, you open the dog book, what does it say?"},{"time":173000,"text":"\"Hold his front paws, squeeze his front paws,"},{"time":175000,"text":"stamp on his hind feet, squirt him in the face with lemon juice,"},{"time":179000,"text":"hit him on the head with a rolled-up newspaper,"},{"time":181000,"text":"knee him in the chest, flip him over backwards.\""},{"time":183000,"text":"Because he grew?"},{"time":185000,"text":"And because he's performing a behavior you've trained him to do?"},{"time":188000,"text":"This is insanity."},{"time":191000,"text":"I ask owners, \"Well, how would you like the dog to greet you?\""},{"time":194000,"text":"And people say, \"Well, I don't know, to sit, I guess.\""},{"time":197000,"text":"I said, \"Let's teach him to sit.\""},{"time":199000,"text":"And then we give him a reason for sitting."},{"time":203000,"text":"Because the first stage"},{"time":206000,"text":"is basically teaching a dog ESL."},{"time":209000,"text":"I could speak to you and say, \"Laytay-chai, paisey, paisey.\""},{"time":214000,"text":"Go on, something should happen now."},{"time":216000,"text":"Why aren't you responding? Oh, you don't speak Swahili."},{"time":219000,"text":"Well, I've got news for you."},{"time":221000,"text":"The dog doesn't speak English, or American, or Spanish, or French."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226000,"text":"So the first stage in training is to teach the dog ESL,"},{"time":229000,"text":"English as a second language."},{"time":231000,"text":"And that's how we use the food lure in the hand,"},{"time":233000,"text":"and we use food because we're dealing with owners."},{"time":236000,"text":"My wife doesn't need food -- she's a great trainer,"},{"time":238000,"text":"much better than I am."},{"time":239000,"text":"I don't need food, but the average owner says,"},{"time":242000,"text":"\"Puppy, sit.\""},{"time":244000,"text":"Or they go, \"Sit, sit, sit.\""},{"time":246000,"text":"They're making a hand signal in front of the dog's rectum for some reason,"},{"time":249000,"text":"like the dog has a third eye there -- it's insane."},{"time":252000,"text":"You know, \"Sit, sit.\""},{"time":254000,"text":"No, we go, \"Puppy, sit\" -- boom, it's got it in six to 10 trials."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"Then we phase out the food as a lure,"},{"time":260000,"text":"and now the dog knows that \"sit\" means sit,"},{"time":262000,"text":"and you can actually communicate to a dog"},{"time":264000,"text":"in a perfectly constructed English sentence."},{"time":266000,"text":"\"Phoenix, come here, take this, and go to Jamie, please.\""},{"time":270000,"text":"And I've taught her \"Phoenix,\" \"come here,\" \"take this,\" \"go to\""},{"time":273000,"text":"and the name of my son, \"Jamie.\""},{"time":275000,"text":"And the dog can take a note,"},{"time":277000,"text":"and I've got my own little search-and-rescue dog."},{"time":279000,"text":"He'll find Jamie wherever he is, you know,"},{"time":281000,"text":"wherever kids are, crushing rocks by a stream or something,"},{"time":283000,"text":"and take him a little message that says,"},{"time":285000,"text":"\"Hey, dinner's ready. Come in for dinner.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":288000,"text":"So, at this point, the dog knows what we want it to do."},{"time":291000,"text":"Will it do it?"},{"time":293000,"text":"Not necessarily, no."},{"time":295000,"text":"As I said, if he's in the park and there's a rear end to sniff,"},{"time":298000,"text":"why come to the owner?"},{"time":300000,"text":"The dog lives with you, the dog can get you any time."},{"time":303000,"text":"The dog can sniff your butt, if you like, when he wants to."},{"time":306000,"text":"At the moment, he's in the park, and you are competing"},{"time":308000,"text":"with smells, and other dogs, and squirrels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311000,"text":"So the second stage in training is to teach the dog to want to do"},{"time":315000,"text":"what we want him to do, and this is very easy."},{"time":318000,"text":"We use the Premack principle."},{"time":320000,"text":"Basically, we follow a low-frequency behavior --"},{"time":322000,"text":"one the dog doesn't want to do --"},{"time":324000,"text":"by a high-frequency behavior, commonly known as a behavior problem,"},{"time":328000,"text":"or a dog hobby -- something the dog does like to do."},{"time":332000,"text":"That will then become a reward for the lower-frequency behavior."},{"time":335000,"text":"So we go, \"sit,\" on the couch; \"sit,\" tummy-rub; \"sit,\""},{"time":339000,"text":"look, I throw a tennis ball; \"sit,\" say hello to that other dog."},{"time":343000,"text":"Yes, we put \"sniff butt\" on queue."},{"time":345000,"text":"\"Sit,\" sniff butt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":347000,"text":"So now all of these distractions that worked against training"},{"time":351000,"text":"now become rewards that work for training."},{"time":354000,"text":"And what we're doing, in essence, is we're teaching the dog, kind of like --"},{"time":359000,"text":"we're letting the dog think that the dog is training us."},{"time":362000,"text":"And I can imagine this dog, you know,"},{"time":364000,"text":"speaking through the fence to, say, an Akita,"},{"time":366000,"text":"saying, \"Wow, my owners, they are so incredibly easy to train."},{"time":370000,"text":"They're like Golden Retrievers."},{"time":372000,"text":"All I have to do is sit, and they do everything."},{"time":374000,"text":"They open doors, they drive my car, they massage me,"},{"time":378000,"text":"they will throw tennis balls,"},{"time":380000,"text":"they will cook for me and serve the food."},{"time":382000,"text":"It's like, if I just sit, that's my command."},{"time":385000,"text":"Then I have my own personal doorman,"},{"time":387000,"text":"chauffeur, masseuse, chef and waiter.\""},{"time":391000,"text":"And now the dog's really happy."},{"time":393000,"text":"And this, to me, is always what training is."},{"time":395000,"text":"So we really motivate the dog to want to do it,"},{"time":398000,"text":"such that the need for punishment seldom comes up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403000,"text":"Now we move to phase three, when now --"},{"time":406000,"text":"there's times, you know, when daddy knows best."},{"time":408000,"text":"And I have a little sign on my fridge, and it says,"},{"time":411000,"text":"\"Because I'm the daddy, that's why.\""},{"time":413000,"text":"Sorry, no more explanation. \"I'm the daddy, you're not. Sit.\""},{"time":417000,"text":"And there's times, for example,"},{"time":419000,"text":"if my son's friends leave the door open,"},{"time":422000,"text":"the dogs have to know you don't step across this line."},{"time":426000,"text":"This is a life-or-death thing."},{"time":428000,"text":"You leave this, the sanctity of your house,"},{"time":431000,"text":"and you could be hit on the street."},{"time":433000,"text":"So some things we have to let the dog know,"},{"time":435000,"text":"\"You mustn't do this.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":437000,"text":"And so we have to enforce, but without force."},{"time":442000,"text":"People here get very confused about what a punishment is."},{"time":446000,"text":"They think a punishment is something nasty."},{"time":448000,"text":"I bet a lot of you do, right?"},{"time":450000,"text":"You think it's something painful, or scary, or nasty."},{"time":453000,"text":"It doesn't have to be."},{"time":455000,"text":"There's several definitions of what a punishment is,"},{"time":458000,"text":"but one definition, the most popular, is:"},{"time":460000,"text":"a punishment is a stimulus that reduces the immediately preceding behavior,"},{"time":465000,"text":"such that it's less likely to occur in the future."},{"time":469000,"text":"It does not have to be nasty, scary or painful."},{"time":474000,"text":"And I would say, if it doesn't have to be, then maybe it shouldn't be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479000,"text":"I was working with a very dangerous dog about a year ago."},{"time":482000,"text":"And this was a dog that put both his owners in hospital,"},{"time":485000,"text":"plus the brother-in-law, plus the child."},{"time":487000,"text":"And I only agreed to work with it if they promised it would stay in their house,"},{"time":490000,"text":"and they never took it outside."},{"time":492000,"text":"The dog is actually euthanized now,"},{"time":494000,"text":"but this was a dog I worked with for a while."},{"time":496000,"text":"A lot of the aggression happened around the kitchen,"},{"time":499000,"text":"so while I was there -- this was on the fourth visit --"},{"time":502000,"text":"we did a four and a half hour down-stay, with the dog on his mat."},{"time":505000,"text":"And he was kept there by the owner's calm insistence."},{"time":510000,"text":"When the dog would try to leave the mat,"},{"time":512000,"text":"she would say, \"Rover, on the mat, on the mat, on the mat.\""},{"time":516000,"text":"The dog broke his down-stay 22 times in four and a half hours, while she cooked dinner,"},{"time":521000,"text":"because we had a lot of aggression related towards food."},{"time":525000,"text":"The breaks got fewer and fewer."},{"time":527000,"text":"You see, the punishment was working."},{"time":530000,"text":"The behavior problem was going away."},{"time":532000,"text":"She never raised her voice."},{"time":534000,"text":"If she did, she would have got bitten."},{"time":537000,"text":"It's not a good dog you shout at."},{"time":539000,"text":"And a lot of my friends train really neat animals,"},{"time":542000,"text":"grizzly bears -- if you've ever seen a grizzly bear"},{"time":544000,"text":"on the telly or in film, then it's a friend of mine who's trained it --"},{"time":547000,"text":"killer whales. I love it because it wires you up."},{"time":550000,"text":"How are you going to reprimand a grizzly bear?"},{"time":552000,"text":"\"Bad bear, bad bear!\" Voom!"},{"time":554000,"text":"Your head now is 100 yards away, sailing through the air, OK?"},{"time":559000,"text":"This is crazy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561000,"text":"So, where do we go from here?"},{"time":563000,"text":"We want a better way."},{"time":565000,"text":"Dogs deserve better."},{"time":567000,"text":"But for me, the reason for this actually has to do with dogs."},{"time":571000,"text":"It has to do with watching people train puppies,"},{"time":574000,"text":"and realizing they have horrendous interaction skills,"},{"time":579000,"text":"horrendous relationship skills."},{"time":581000,"text":"Not just with their puppy, but with the rest of the family at class."},{"time":585000,"text":"I mean, my all-time classic is another \"come here\" one."},{"time":588000,"text":"You see someone in the park -- and I'll cover my mic when I say this,"},{"time":591000,"text":"because I don't want to wake you up -- and there's the owner in the park,"},{"time":594000,"text":"and their dog's over here, and they say, \"Rover, come here."},{"time":596000,"text":"Rover, come here. Rover, come here, you son of a bitch.\""},{"time":600000,"text":"The dog says, \"I don't think so.\""},{"time":602000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":603000,"text":"I mean, who in their right mind"},{"time":606000,"text":"would think that a dog would want to approach them"},{"time":609000,"text":"when they're screaming like that?"},{"time":611000,"text":"Instead, the dog says, \"I know that tone. I know that tone."},{"time":614000,"text":"Previously, when I've approached, I've gotten punished there.\""},{"time":617000,"text":"I was walking onto a plane --"},{"time":619000,"text":"this, for me, was a pivotal moment in my career,"},{"time":622000,"text":"and it really cemented what I wanted to do"},{"time":624000,"text":"with this whole puppy-training thing,"},{"time":626000,"text":"the notion of how to teach puppies in a dog-friendly way"},{"time":630000,"text":"to want to do what we want to do, so we don't have to force them."},{"time":633000,"text":"You know, I puppy-train my child."},{"time":636000,"text":"And the seminal moment was, I was getting on a plane in Dallas,"},{"time":639000,"text":"and in row two was a father, I presume, and a young boy about five,"},{"time":643000,"text":"kicking the back of the chair."},{"time":645000,"text":"\"Johnny, don't do that.\""},{"time":647000,"text":"Kick, kick, kick."},{"time":648000,"text":"\"Johnny, don't do that.\" Kick, kick, kick."},{"time":650000,"text":"I'm standing right here with my bag."},{"time":652000,"text":"The father leans over, grabs him like this and gives him ugly face."},{"time":656000,"text":"And ugly face is this --"},{"time":658000,"text":"when you go face-to-face with a puppy or a child,"},{"time":661000,"text":"you say, \"What are you doing! Now stop it, stop it, stop it!\""},{"time":664000,"text":"And I went, \"Oh my God, do I do something?\""},{"time":667000,"text":"That child has lost everything --"},{"time":670000,"text":"that one of the two people he can trust in this world"},{"time":673000,"text":"has absolutely pulled the rug from under his feet."},{"time":676000,"text":"And I thought, \"Do I tell this jerk to quit it?\""},{"time":678000,"text":"I thought, \"Ian, stay out of it, stay out of it, you know, walk on.\""},{"time":681000,"text":"I walked to the back of the plane,"},{"time":683000,"text":"I sat down, and a thought came to me."},{"time":686000,"text":"If that had been a dog, I would have laid him out."},{"time":688000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":689000,"text":"If he had kicked a dog, I would have punched him out."},{"time":693000,"text":"He kicked a child, grabs the child like this and I let it go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698000,"text":"And this is what it's all about."},{"time":701000,"text":"These relationship skills are so easy."},{"time":703000,"text":"I mean, we as humans, our shallowness when we choose a life-mate"},{"time":708000,"text":"based on the three Cs -- coat color, conformation, cuteness."},{"time":712000,"text":"You know, kind of like a little robot."},{"time":714000,"text":"This is how we go into a relationship, and it's hunky-dory for a year."},{"time":717000,"text":"And then, a little behavior problem comes up."},{"time":719000,"text":"No different from the dog barking."},{"time":721000,"text":"The husband won't clear up his clothes,"},{"time":723000,"text":"or the wife's always late for meetings, whatever it is, OK?"},{"time":727000,"text":"And it then starts, and we get into this thing,"},{"time":731000,"text":"and our personal feedback -- there's two things about it."},{"time":733000,"text":"When you watch people interacting with animals or other people,"},{"time":736000,"text":"there is very little feedback, it's too infrequent."},{"time":740000,"text":"And when it happens, it's bad, it's nasty."},{"time":743000,"text":"You see it's especially in families, especially with spouses,"},{"time":748000,"text":"especially with children, especially with parents."},{"time":751000,"text":"You see it especially in the workplace,"},{"time":753000,"text":"especially from boss to employee."},{"time":755000,"text":"It's as if there's some schadenfreude there,"},{"time":758000,"text":"that we actually take delight in people getting things wrong,"},{"time":761000,"text":"so that we can then moan and groan and bitch at them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":766000,"text":"And this, I would say, is the biggest human foible that we have."},{"time":770000,"text":"It really is."},{"time":772000,"text":"We take the good for granted, and we moan and groan at the bad."},{"time":775000,"text":"And I think this whole notion of these skills should be taught."},{"time":778000,"text":"You know, calculus is wonderful."},{"time":780000,"text":"When I was a kid, I was a calculus whiz."},{"time":782000,"text":"I don't understand a thing about it now, but I could do it as a kid."},{"time":786000,"text":"Geometry, fantastic. You know, quantum mechanics --"},{"time":789000,"text":"these are cool things."},{"time":791000,"text":"But they don't save marriages and they don't raise children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":795000,"text":"And my look to the future is,"},{"time":797000,"text":"and what I want to do with this doggy stuff, is to teach people"},{"time":800000,"text":"that you know, your husband's just as easy to train."},{"time":803000,"text":"Probably easier -- if you got a Rottie -- much easier to train."},{"time":808000,"text":"Your kids are easy to train."},{"time":810000,"text":"All you've got to do is to watch them,"},{"time":812000,"text":"to time-sample the behavior, and say, every five minutes,"},{"time":814000,"text":"you ask the question, \"Is it good, or is it bad?\""},{"time":817000,"text":"If it's good, say, \"That was really neat, thank you.\""},{"time":820000,"text":"That is such a powerful training technique."},{"time":822000,"text":"This should be taught in schools."},{"time":824000,"text":"Relationships -- how do you negotiate?"},{"time":826000,"text":"How you do negotiate with your friend who wants your toy?"},{"time":829000,"text":"You know, how to prepare you for your first relationship?"},{"time":832000,"text":"How on earth about raising children?"},{"time":834000,"text":"We think how we do it -- one night in bed, we're pregnant,"},{"time":836000,"text":"and then we're raising the most important thing in life, a child."},{"time":839000,"text":"No, this is what should be taught -- the good living, the good habits,"},{"time":844000,"text":"which are just as hard to break as bad habits."},{"time":848000,"text":"So, that would be my wish to the future."},{"time":850000,"text":"Ah, damn, I wanted to end exactly on time,"},{"time":852000,"text":"but I got eight, seven, six, five, four, three, two --"},{"time":858000,"text":"so thank you very much. That's my talk, thank you."},{"time":860000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}